The paper focuses on measuring the variability in decision making between security professionals, which is a key aspect of cyber-security research (cs.CR). It also aims to improve the quality of security advice given to software system designers, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper uses methods of aggregating opinions and produces an assessment of attacks from ratings of their components, which involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The study involves experts assessing a realistic system scenario, which could involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with cyber-security, which is a subfield of computer science (cs.CY).
